{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871386822,"sessionID":"ses_285d23ea9ffe541yeYBmDfcCbh","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2df598001ijRcUeti7K9Yfz","messageID":"msg_d7a2de732001NsuBVuA8xrMJT1","sessionID":"ses_285d23ea9ffe541yeYBmDfcCbh","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_8f2d75e082244e03acded140","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","content":"# AgentCube Project Proposal\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nAgentCube is a comprehensive developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management, providing a CLI toolkit (`kubectl-agentcube`), Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`), and Kubernetes integration for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and monitoring AI agents on standard Kubernetes or AgentCube-enhanced clusters.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\nAgentCube addresses the operational complexity of deploying and managing AI agents in Kubernetes environments by providing:\n\n- **Unified CLI**: A Typer-based command-line interface for end-to-end agent lifecycle operations\n- **Python SDK**: Programmatic access to Code Interpreter and AgentRuntime services\n- **Dual Provider Support**: Flexible deployment to standard Kubernetes (Deployment + NodePort Service) or AgentCube's custom AgentRuntime CRD\n- **Multi-Language Support**: Python and Java agent workspaces with language-specific validation and Dockerfile generation\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope\n\n### 2.1 Components\n\n| Component | Module Path | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| CLI Toolkit | `cmd/cli` | `kubectl-agentcube` command-line tool |\n| Python SDK | `sdk-python` | `agentcube-sdk` Python client library |\n| Client-Go | `client-go` | Generated Go client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |\n\n### 2.2 CLI Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `pack` | Validate workspace, merge metadata, generate Dockerfile |\n| `build` | Build container image (local Docker or cloud) |\n| `publish` | Deploy to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment) |\n| `invoke` | Send JSON payloads to deployed agents |\n| `status` | Display agent deployment status |\n\n### 2.3 SDK Clients\n\n| Client | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | Create sessions, execute code, manage files |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | Invoke deployed agents via Router |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis\n\n### 3.1 User Impact\n\n**Developers** gain:\n- Single command packaging with automatic Dockerfile generation\n- Context-manager-based SDK with automatic session lifecycle management\n- Consistent error handling with verbose traceback options\n\n**Platform Teams** gain:\n- Standard Kubernetes provider using native Deployment/Service resources\n- AgentCube provider leveraging custom AgentRuntime CRD for advanced features\n- Namespace isolation and readiness probe integration\n\n### 3.2 Technical Impact\n\n**Dependencies** (Python 3.10+):\n- CLI: `typer`, `pydantic`, `pyyaml`, `httpx`, `docker`, `rich`, `kubernetes` (optional)\n- SDK: `requests`, `PyJWT`, `cryptography`\n\n**Kubernetes API**:\n- Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- Version: `v1alpha1`\n- Resources: `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`\n\n**Metadata Schema**:\n- Canonical file: `agent_metadata.yaml` (fallbacks: `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`)\n- Pydantic-validated fields: `agent_name`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`, `build_mode`, `image`, `k8s_deployment`\n\n### 3.3 Operational Considerations\n\n| Concern | Mitigation |\n|---------|------------|\n| Docker availability | Explicit `DockerService.check_docker_available()` before local builds |\n| Kubernetes readiness | `wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)` with `TimeoutError` on failure |\n| Session management | Automatic bootstrap + cleanup via context managers |\n| Version control | Automatic patch increment on build with rollback on failure |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered\n\n### 4.1 Metadata File Naming\n\n| Option | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|--------|------|------|----------|\n| `agentcube.yaml` | Aligns with project name | Inconsistent with implementation | Rejected |\n| `agent.yaml` | Short, generic | May conflict with other tools | Fallback only |\n| `agent_metadata.yaml` | Explicit purpose, matches code | Slightly verbose | **Canonical** |\n\n### 4.2 Provider Model\n\n| Option | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|--------|------|------|----------|\n| Kubernetes-only | Simpler implementation | Loses AgentCube-specific features | Insufficient |\n| AgentCube-only | Full feature access | Requires AgentCube platform | Too restrictive |\n| Dual provider | Maximum flexibility | Increased complexity | **Selected** |\n\n### 4.3 Session Header Casing\n\n| Option | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|--------|------|------|----------|\n| `X-AgentCube-Session-Id` | Title-case convention | Inconsistent with Router expectations | Rejected |\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | Matches Router implementation | Lowercase may seem informal | **Selected** |\n\n### 4.4 SDK Configuration\n\n| Option | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|--------|------|------|----------|\n| Central `Configuration` class | Single source of truth | Boilerplate, rigid | Rejected |\n| Distributed resolution | Flexible per-client, env-friendly | Harder to audit defaults | **Selected** |\n\n### 4.5 Build Mode\n\n| Option | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|--------|------|------|----------|\n| Local-only | Faster iteration, no cloud dependency | Requires local Docker | Default |\n| Cloud-only | No local Docker requirement | Network dependency, slower | Alternative |\n| Hybrid (configurable) | Best of both | Metadata complexity | **Selected** |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    kubectl-agentcube CLI                     │\n│  (pack → build → publish → invoke → status)                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n            ┌─────────────────┴─────────────────┐\n            │                                   │\n   ┌────────▼────────┐                 ┌────────▼────────┐\n   │  Runtime Classes│                 │   Services      │\n   │  - PackRuntime  │                 │  - DockerService│\n   │  - BuildRuntime │                 │  - MetadataSvc  │\n   │  - PublishRt    │                 │  - K8sProvider  │\n   │  - InvokeRt     │                 │  - ACCubeProvider│\n   │  - StatusRt     │                 │                 │\n   └─────────────────┘                 └─────────────────┘\n            │                                   │\n            └─────────────────┬─────────────────┘\n                              │\n            ┌─────────────────┼─────────────────┐\n            │                 │                 │\n   ┌────────▼────┐   ┌────────▼────┐   ┌────────▼────┐\n   │   Docker    │   │  Kubernetes │   │ AgentCube   │\n   │   Daemon    │   │   Cluster   │   │   Platform  │\n   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Status\n\n### 6.1 CLI Toolkit (`cmd/cli`)\n\n| Module | Status | Notes |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Implemented | Typer app, all commands, error handling |\n| `agentcube/runtime/*` | Implemented | 5 runtime classes with full lifecycle |\n| `agentcube/services/*` | Implemented | Docker, K8s, AgentCube providers |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Implemented | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Implemented | `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model |\n\n**Known Issues**:\n- `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube`: `UnboundLocalError` risk if `endpoint` doesn't start with `\"http:\"` (line ~200)\n\n### 6.2 Python SDK (`sdk-python`)\n\n| Module | Status | Notes |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | Implemented | Context manager, full lifecycle |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | Implemented | Bootstrap session, invoke |\n| `agentcube/clients/*` | Implemented | Control plane + data plane clients |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Implemented | Hierarchy defined (partial usage) |\n\n**Notes**:\n- `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core clients\n- SDK relies on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, `CommandExecutionError`\n\n### 6.3 Client-Go (`client-go`)\n\n| Component | Status | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Typed clients | Generated | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, `CodeInterpreterInterface` |\n| Informers | Generated | `SharedInformerFactory`, per-type informers |\n| Listers | Generated | Namespace-scoped listers |\n| Fake clients | Generated | Test doubles for unit testing |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Testing Strategy\n\n### 7.1 CLI Testing\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\"\n]\n```\n\n**Test Categories**:\n- Unit: Runtime classes with mocked services\n- Integration: Docker/Kubernetes interactions (requires environment)\n- CLI: Typer command invocation with `CliRunner`\n\n### 7.2 SDK Testing\n\n**Test Files**:\n- `tests/test_code_interpreter.py`\n- `tests/test_agent_runtime.py`\n- `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n- `tests/test_data_plane.py`\n\n**E2E**: `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` (requires PicoD environment)\n\n---\n\n## 8. Documentation Gaps\n\n| Gap | Risk | Recommendation |\n|-----|------|----------------|\n| `agentcube.yaml` vs `agent_metadata.yaml` | User confusion | Update docs to reflect canonical name |\n| `StatusRuntime` not in `__all__` | Discoverability | Consider adding to exports |\n| `SessionError`/`DataPlaneError` unused | Inconsistent error handling | Audit for usage or remove |\n| `UnboundLocalError` in invoke | Runtime crash | Fix conditional assignment |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Recommendations\n\n### 9.1 Immediate (P0)\n\n1. **Fix `UnboundLocalError`** in `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n2. **Standardize metadata filename** in documentation to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n3. **Add `StatusRuntime` to `__all__`** for consistent discoverability\n\n### 9.2 Short-Term (P1)\n\n1. **Implement `SessionError`/`DataPlaneError` usage** or remove from hierarchy\n2. **Add integration tests** for dual-provider publish flow\n3. **Document environment variables**: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `KUBECONFIG`\n\n### 9.3 Long-Term (P2)\n\n1. **Consider Go SDK** to match client-go generation\n2. **Add `agentcube config` command** for environment setup\n3. **Implement workspace scaffolding** (`agentcube init`)\n\n---\n\n## 10. Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Verification |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| CLI installs and runs | `pip install .` + `kubectl-agentcube --version` |\n| All 5 commands functional | E2E test with sample workspace |\n| SDK context managers work | `with CodeInterpreterClient() as client:` block |\n| Dual provider support | Deploy to both `agentcube` and `k8s` providers |\n| Metadata schema validated | Pydantic rejects invalid `language`/`port` |\n| Client-go compiles | `go build ./client-go/...` |\n\n---\n\n## Appendix A: Example Workflows\n\n### A.1 CLI: Full Lifecycle\n\n```bash\n# Package agent\nkubectl-agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent --language python\n\n# Build image (local Docker)\nkubectl-agentcube build\n\n# Publish to AgentCube\nkubectl-agentcube publish \\\n  --provider agentcube \\\n  --version v1.0.0 \\\n  --region us-west-2\n\n# Invoke agent\nkubectl-agentcube invoke \\\n  --payload '{\"message\": \"Hello\"}' \\\n  --header 'Authorization: Bearer token'\n\n# Check status\nkubectl-agentcube status\n```\n\n### A.2 SDK: Code Interpreter\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-interpreter\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"https://router.example.com\",\n) as client:\n    result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello')\")\n    client.upload_file(\"local.py\", \"/workspace/remote.py\")\n# Automatic session cleanup on exit\n```\n\n### A.3 SDK: Agent Runtime\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"https://router.example.com\",\n) as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is 2+2?\"})\n    print(response.json())\n```\n\n---\n\n## Appendix B: API Reference Summary\n\n### B.1 CRD: AgentRuntime\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: my-agent\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  image: registry.example.com/my-agent:latest\n  port: 8080\n  sessionTimeout: 15m\n  maxSessionDuration: 8h\n  env:\n    - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n      value: http://workload-manager:8080\n    - name: ROUTER_URL\n      value: http://router:8080\n  readinessProbe:\n    path: /health\n    port: 8080\n  imagePullSecrets:\n    - name: default-secret\n```\n\n### B.2 Metadata Schema\n\n```yaml\n# agent_metadata.yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\ndescription: Example agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nversion: v1.0.0\nregion: us-west-2\nimage:\n  name: registry.example.com/my-agent\n  tag: v1.0.0\n  image_id: sha256:...\nagent_endpoint: http://localhost:30000\nworkload_manager_url: http://workload-manager:8080\nrouter_url: http://router:8080\nreadiness_probe_path: /health\nreadiness_probe_port: 8080\n```\n\n---\n\n**Document Version**: 1.0  \n**Last Updated**: 2026-04-11  \n**Author**: AgentCube Team  \n**Contact**: agentcube@volcano.sh\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775871386811,"end":1775871386819}}}}
