{"type":"text","timestamp":1775871400371,"sessionID":"ses_285d23ea9ffe541yeYBmDfcCbh","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2f1738001Rfz747a0gaWcS1","messageID":"msg_d7a2f081c001aASClDVKaIW3GZ","sessionID":"ses_285d23ea9ffe541yeYBmDfcCbh","type":"text","text":"I see there's already a `proposal.md` file for a different AR (AR-011: Router JWT Authentication). Based on the task in `.sdd_prompt.md`, I need to write a proposal for **AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型** for the AgentCube CLI project. Let me create the appropriate proposal:","time":{"start":1775871400370,"end":1775871400370}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871498700,"sessionID":"ses_285d23ea9ffe541yeYBmDfcCbh","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2f19b4001azSJzu4csgqcou","messageID":"msg_d7a2f081c001aASClDVKaIW3GZ","sessionID":"ses_285d23ea9ffe541yeYBmDfcCbh","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_cc9ef019bd8f4bfdbd2d9653","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `MetadataService` and associated data models for the AgentCube CLI toolkit (`cmd/cli`). The goal is to:\n\n1. **Centralize metadata management** - Provide a single source of truth for agent configuration across the CLI\n2. **Enable workspace validation** - Validate agent workspace structure and language-specific requirements\n3. **Support metadata lifecycle** - Load, save, update, and validate agent metadata throughout the agent lifecycle\n4. **Ensure schema correctness** - Use Pydantic validation to enforce metadata schema constraints\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with all required fields and validators\n  - `MetadataService` class with load/save/update/validate operations\n  - `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI option mapping\n  - Workspace validation for Python and Java agents\n  - YAML persistence with fallback file naming\n  - Integration with `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - CLI command implementations (separate ARs)\n  - Docker/Kubernetes service integrations\n  - AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRD operations\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Implementation\n\nPer the design specification (`cli-toolkit/design.md`), the following components exist:\n\n1. **Package Layout:**\n   - `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` - `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService`\n   - `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` - `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n   - `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` - Uses `MetadataService` internally\n\n2. **AgentMetadata Fields:**\n   - Core: `agent_name`, `description`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`, `build_mode`, `version`\n   - Image: `image`, `auth`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`\n   - Deployment: `region`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`\n   - Probes: `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n   - Runtime: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n\n3. **Validators:**\n   - `validate_language` - Restricts to `['python', 'java']`\n   - `validate_build_mode` - Restricts to `['local', 'cloud']`\n   - `validate_port` - Range `1..65535`\n\n4. **MetadataService Methods:**\n   - `load_metadata(workspace_path)` - Load from YAML with fallbacks\n   - `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` - Persist to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n   - `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` - Partial update helper\n   - `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` - Structure validation\n   - `_validate_python_workspace(...)` - Python-specific checks\n   - `_validate_java_workspace(...)` - Java-specific checks\n\n### Issues Identified\n\n1. **Documentation drift** - Some docs reference `agentcube.yaml` instead of canonical `agent_metadata.yaml`\n2. **Discoverability** - `StatusRuntime` not exported in `__all__` despite being part of runtime suite\n3. **Incomplete error handling** - `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but unused in SDK\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. AgentMetadata Model\n\nDefine comprehensive Pydantic model in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`:\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Agent metadata schema with validation.\"\"\"\n    \n    # Core identification\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    \n    # Language and execution\n    language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    \n    # Build configuration\n    build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n    version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n    region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n    \n    # Dependency management\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n    \n    # Image registry\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n    \n    # Runtime endpoints\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n    router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n    \n    # Health probes\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n    \n    # Runtime state\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n    session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n    \n    # Deployment info\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n    \n    # Validators\n    @field_validator(\"language\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        v = v.lower()\n        if v not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n            raise ValueError(\"language must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n        return v\n    \n    @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        v = v.lower()\n        if v not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n            raise ValueError(\"build_mode must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n        return v\n    \n    @field_validator(\"port\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n        if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n            raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n        return v\n```\n\n### 2. MetadataService Implementation\n\nImplement service class in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`:\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    \"\"\"Service for agent metadata management.\"\"\"\n    \n    METADATA_FILES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n    \n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n    \n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace, trying fallback filenames.\"\"\"\n        for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n            metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n            if metadata_file.exists():\n                try:\n                    content = metadata_file.read_text()\n                    data = yaml.safe_load(content)\n                    return AgentMetadata(**data)\n                except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n                    raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {filename}: {e}\")\n                except ValidationError as e:\n                    raise ValueError(f\"Invalid metadata schema: {e}\")\n        \n        # No metadata file found - return defaults\n        return AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=workspace_path.name,\n            entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        )\n    \n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Save metadata to canonical filename.\"\"\"\n        metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n        content = yaml.dump(\n            data,\n            default_flow_style=False,\n            indent=2,\n            sort_keys=False,\n        )\n        metadata_file.write_text(content)\n    \n    def update_metadata(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        updates: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load, update, save, and return metadata.\"\"\"\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        updated = metadata.model_copy(update=updates)\n        self.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated)\n        return updated\n    \n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace structure and content.\"\"\"\n        if not workspace_path.exists():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n        \n        if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n        \n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        \n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        return True\n    \n    def _validate_python_workspace(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n        py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if not py_files:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n    \n    def _validate_java_workspace(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n        pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n        if not pom_xml.exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")\n```\n\n### 3. MetadataOptions Dataclass\n\nDefine options class in `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"CLI options mapped to metadata fields.\"\"\"\n    \n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        \"\"\"Create from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n        return cls(\n            agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n            language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n            entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n            port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n            build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n            requirements_file=options.get(\"requirements_file\"),\n            description=options.get(\"description\"),\n            workload_manager_url=options.get(\"workload_manager_url\", \"\"),\n            router_url=options.get(\"router_url\", \"\"),\n            readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\", \"\"),\n            readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\", 8080),\n            registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\", \"\"),\n            registry_username=options.get(\"registry_username\", \"\"),\n            registry_password=options.get(\"registry_password\", \"\"),\n            agent_endpoint=options.get(\"agent_endpoint\", \"\"),\n        )\n```\n\n### 4. Integration with PackRuntime\n\nUpdate `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` to use `MetadataService`:\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n    \n    def pack(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        **options: Any,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Package agent workspace.\"\"\"\n        # Validate workspace structure\n        self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n        \n        # Load or create metadata\n        metadata_options = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\n        metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, metadata_options)\n        \n        # Apply CLI overrides\n        metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, metadata_options)\n        \n        # Validate language compatibility\n        self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        # Process dependencies\n        self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        # Generate Dockerfile\n        dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        # Update metadata with packaging info\n        self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n        \n        # Prepare output\n        final_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n        \n        return {\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"workspace_path\": str(final_path),\n            \"metadata_path\": str(final_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n            \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n        }\n    \n    def _load_or_create_metadata(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        options: MetadataOptions,\n    ) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create new.\"\"\"\n        try:\n            metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        except (FileNotFoundError, ValueError):\n            # Create new metadata with defaults\n            metadata = AgentMetadata(\n                agent_name=options.agent_name or workspace_path.name,\n                language=options.language or \"python\",\n                entrypoint=options.entrypoint or \"python main.py\",\n                port=options.port or 8080,\n                build_mode=options.build_mode or \"local\",\n            )\n        return metadata\n```\n\n### 5. Module Exports\n\nUpdate `agentcube/__init__.py` to include `StatusRuntime`:\n\n```python\n__version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"\n__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n\nfrom agentcube.cli.main import app\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"app\",\n    \"PackRuntime\",\n    \"BuildRuntime\",\n    \"PublishRuntime\",\n    \"InvokeRuntime\",\n    \"StatusRuntime\",  # Added for consistency\n]\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n| File | Changes | Impact |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Implement `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` | High - core functionality |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Integrate `MetadataService` | Medium - uses service |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Export `StatusRuntime` | Low - additive |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-export `MetadataOptions` | Low - convenience |\n\n### Dependencies\n\nFrom `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",      # For AgentMetadata\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",          # For YAML persistence\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n    \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n]\n```\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- **Metadata file naming**: Canonical `agent_metadata.yaml` with fallbacks to `agent.yaml` and `metadata.yaml`\n- **Schema evolution**: Pydantic `Optional` fields allow gradual adoption\n- **Default values**: Sensible defaults minimize required configuration\n\n### Testing Impact\n\nUnit tests required for:\n\n- `AgentMetadata` validation (language, build_mode, port)\n- `MetadataService.load_metadata()` with all fallback files\n- `MetadataService.save_metadata()` YAML format\n- `MetadataService.validate_workspace()` for Python and Java\n- `MetadataOptions.from_options()` mapping\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: JSON Metadata\n\nUse JSON instead of YAML for metadata persistence.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Native Python support (no extra dependency)\n- Faster parsing\n- Strict syntax\n\n**Cons:**\n- Less human-readable\n- No comments support\n- Inconsistent with Kubernetes manifests\n\n**Decision:** YAML is preferred for consistency with Kubernetes ecosystem.\n\n### Alternative 2: Configuration Dataclass\n\nUse a simple dataclass instead of Pydantic model.\n\n**Pros:**\n- No external dependency\n- Simpler implementation\n- Faster instantiation\n\n**Cons:**\n- No built-in validation\n- Manual type checking\n- No serialization helpers\n\n**Decision:** Pydantic provides essential validation and serialization.\n\n### Alternative 3: Environment Variables Only\n\nStore configuration in environment variables instead of files.\n\n**Pros:**\n- No file management\n- Easy for containers\n- Secret-friendly\n\n**Cons:**\n- No persistence\n- Hard to version\n- Poor discoverability\n\n**Decision:** File-based metadata with optional env overrides.\n\n### Alternative 4: Central Configuration Class\n\nCreate a `Configuration` class like the Python SDK pattern.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Single source of truth\n- Easier to audit defaults\n- Consistent interface\n\n**Cons:**\n- More boilerplate\n- Less flexible per-component\n- Overkill for CLI\n\n**Decision:** Distributed resolution (per spec) is more flexible.\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Implement `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with validators\n- [ ] Implement `MetadataService` with load/save/update/validate\n- [ ] Create `MetadataOptions` dataclass with `from_options()`\n- [ ] Update `PackRuntime` to use `MetadataService`\n- [ ] Export `StatusRuntime` in `agentcube/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write unit tests for metadata validation\n- [ ] Write integration tests for workspace validation\n- [ ] Update documentation to reflect `agent_metadata.yaml` naming\n- [ ] Add example `agent_metadata.yaml` to examples/\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/test_metadata_service.py\n\nclass TestAgentMetadata:\n    def test_valid_metadata(self):\n        metadata = AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n            language=\"python\",\n            port=8080,\n        )\n        assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n        assert metadata.port == 8080\n    \n    def test_invalid_language(self):\n        with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n            AgentMetadata(\n                agent_name=\"test\",\n                entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n                language=\"golang\",\n            )\n    \n    def test_invalid_port(self):\n        with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n            AgentMetadata(\n                agent_name=\"test\",\n                entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n                port=70000,\n            )\n\n\nclass TestMetadataService:\n    def test_load_metadata_primary(self, tmp_path):\n        metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        metadata_file.write_text(\"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\")\n        \n        service = MetadataService()\n        metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n        \n        assert metadata.agent_name == \"test\"\n    \n    def test_load_metadata_fallback(self, tmp_path):\n        # Only agent.yaml exists\n        metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent.yaml\"\n        metadata_file.write_text(\"agent_name: fallback-test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\")\n        \n        service = MetadataService()\n        metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n        \n        assert metadata.agent_name == \"fallback-test\"\n    \n    def test_validate_python_workspace_no_files(self, tmp_path):\n        service = MetadataService()\n        \n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"No Python files found\"):\n            service.validate_workspace(tmp_path)\n    \n    def test_validate_java_workspace_no_pom(self, tmp_path):\n        # Create a Python file to satisfy language detection\n        (tmp_path / \"Main.java\").write_text(\"public class Main {}\")\n        \n        service = MetadataService()\n        # Manually set language to java\n        metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        metadata_file.write_text(\n            \"agent_name: java-test\\nentrypoint: java Main\\nlanguage: java\"\n        )\n        \n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"pom.xml not found\"):\n            service.validate_workspace(tmp_path)\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pack_runtime.py\n\nclass TestPackRuntimeIntegration:\n    def test_full_pack_flow(self, tmp_path):\n        # Create workspace structure\n        (tmp_path / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n        (tmp_path / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"requests\\n\")\n        \n        runtime = PackRuntime()\n        result = runtime.pack(tmp_path)\n        \n        assert \"agent_name\" in result\n        assert \"metadata_path\" in result\n        assert (tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").exists()\n```\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Metadata versioning** - Schema version field for migration support\n2. **Secret management** - Integrate with Kubernetes secrets or external vaults\n3. **Metadata templates** - Pre-configured templates for common agent types\n4. **Validation plugins** - Extensible validation for custom languages\n5. **Metadata diff/patch** - Track changes across packaging operations\n6. **Workspace scaffolding** - `agentcube init` command to create workspace structure\n\n## References\n\n- CLI Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- CLI Specification: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n- Python SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Pydantic Docs: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n- YAML Spec: https://yaml.org/spec/\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Verification |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| `AgentMetadata` validates language | Pydantic rejects non-python/java |\n| `AgentMetadata` validates port | Rejects ports outside 1-65535 |\n| `MetadataService` loads primary file | Finds `agent_metadata.yaml` first |\n| `MetadataService` uses fallbacks | Loads `agent.yaml` if primary missing |\n| `MetadataService` saves correctly | Writes valid YAML with correct format |\n| Workspace validation works | Python requires .py, Java requires pom.xml |\n| `MetadataOptions.from_options()` maps | CLI dict converts to dataclass |\n| `StatusRuntime` exported | `from agentcube import StatusRuntime` works |\n\n---\n\n**Document Version:** 1.0  \n**Last Updated:** 2026-04-11  \n**Author:** AgentCube Team  \n**Contact:** agentcube@volcano.sh  \n**AR:** AR-025  \n**Module:** `cmd/cli`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871498580,"end":1775871498697}}}}
